  "riddle": "1. Track down the classic Japanese teen-pop single that once caught hearts; what was its peak position on the Oricon singles chart?\n\n2. Now take that number and seek its digital root — iteratively sum its digits until only a single digit remains.\n\n3. In what year did a survey conducted by a prominent broadcasting organization begin to influence the very characteristics of this music genre?\n\n4. Turn your attention to the page that holds the tradition of a celebrated year-end music competition. How many contests have been mentioned in its infobox?\n\n5. Go explore a source for Japan’s music sales — how many retail outlets contributed to the charting as of April 2011?\n\n6. An article speaks of popular melodies resonating across borders; in how many different languages is it available?\n\n7. Find out in what year the compact disc format, particularly CD3s, began to fade from the charts in the United States.\n\n8. Seek the format known for its large diameter — what is the measurement in inches of the twelve-inch single?\n\n9. Journey to a legendary gathering where music fans unite; how many attended its inaugural festival?\n\n10. A stately estate intended for summer enjoyment might be your next clue; what location does this home boast within its infobox?\n\n11. Investigate the height above sea level at Knebworth Park; what is its elevation?\n\n12. Reflect on the location you have just discovered; what is the alphabetical position of its first letter?\n\n13. Uncover the total length of the ring road that circles the bustling metropolis of Chennai.\n\n14. Ascend once more to find how high the ground sits along this significant roadway in Chennai.\n\n15. Discover how many parks can be found in proximity to this busy ring road — what’s the count?\n\n16. Combine the elevation found in clue 14 with the number of parks identified in clue 15; what do they amount to?\n\n17. From your previous journey, calculate the digital root of the total length discovered in clue 13 — what remains?\n\n18. Seek the distance of another important thoroughfare known for its connectivity; how long is this road in kilometers?\n\n19. Ascertain the elevation along this pivotal road — how high is it above sea level?\n\n20. Investigate how many libraries are located near this route — what is the count?\n\n21. Combine the elevation from clue 19 with the number of libraries from clue 20; add these two figures together.\n\n22. Seek out the next prime number that follows the result from clue 18; what is this special integer?\n\n23. Find the train station with numerous platforms listed; what number is shown in its infobox?\n\n24. Investigate the elevation of this transit hub — what is its height in meters?\n\n25. A rating matters for travel; what is the Google rating of this railway station?\n\n26. Add the elevation from clue 24 to the Google rating from clue 25; what’s the total?\n\n27. Look into the vast population of this nation filled with culture and vibrancy; how many reside there?\n\n28. Query the same for the land of tea and spices; what is its population?\n\n29. Venture on to another resource for the previous population; confirm the number there too.\n\n30. What’s the next prime number following the largest population figure you just gathered?\n\n31. Count how many stadiums exist near a vibrant urban area known for its cricket love; what’s the total?\n\n32. Compute the digital root of the values obtained from clues 11, 12, and 18 — remember to add them first before finding that single digit! \n\nThe result will yield a number that holds a single digit (0-9).",
